The paper deals with distributed iterative algorithms for receiver cooperation in interference-limited wireless systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and communications (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of probabilistic models and message-passing tools also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
